ğŸ”¹ Largest Rectangle in Histogram
1ï¸âƒ£ Pattern ko kaise pehchaane?
Question bole: â€œGiven bar heights of histogram, find largest rectangle areaâ€
Agar maximum area under histogram ya largest rectangle in histogram likha ho â†’ Monotonic Stack ka pattern use hoga.
Keywords:
â€œLargest rectangle areaâ€
â€œHistogram barsâ€
â€œMax rectangle under skylineâ€

2ï¸âƒ£ Logic / Algorithm
Har bar ke liye humko next smaller element (NSE) aur previous smaller element (PSE) find karna hai.
PSE â†’ left boundary
NSE â†’ right boundary
Rectangle width = right_index - left_index - 1
Area = height * width
Maximum area find karo across all bars.
Stack trick:
Maintain a monotonic increasing stack (heights)
Jab current bar chhota ho â†’ stack se pop kar ke area calculate karo.
Ye logic NSE + PSE dono ka kaam ek saath kar deta hai.

3ï¸âƒ£ Example + Dry Run
Histogram: heights = [2,1,5,6,2,3]
Stack use karenge indices ka.
i=0 â†’ 2 â†’ stack empty â†’ push(0) â†’ stack=[0]
i=1 â†’ 1 < 2 â†’ pop(0) â†’ height=2, width=i=1 â†’ area=2 â†’ max_area=2 â†’ push(1) â†’ stack=[1]
i=2 â†’ 5 > 1 â†’ push(2) â†’ stack=[1,2]
i=3 â†’ 6 > 5 â†’ push(3) â†’ stack=[1,2,3]
i=4 â†’ 2 < 6 â†’ pop(3) â†’ height=6, width=4-2-1=1 â†’ area=6 â†’ max_area=6 â†’ 2 < 5 â†’ pop(2) â†’ height=5, width=4-1-1=2 â†’ area=10 â†’ max_area=10 â†’ push(4) â†’ stack=[1,4]
i=5 â†’ 3 > 2 â†’ push(5) â†’ stack=[1,4,5]

Finally, flush remaining stack:
pop(5) â†’ height=3, width=6-4-1=1 â†’ area=3
pop(4) â†’ height=2, width=6-1-1=4 â†’ area=8
pop(1) â†’ height=1, width=6-(-1)-1=6 â†’ area=6
âœ… Max Area = 10

Time Complexity: O(n) â†’ har element max ek baar push aur pop hota hai
Space Complexity: O(n) â†’ stack use hota hai

class Solution {
public:
    int largestRectangleArea(vector<int>& heights) {
        stack<int> st;
        int maxArea = 0;
        int n = heights.size();
        
        for(int i=0; i<=n; i++) {
            int currHeight = (i==n ? 0 : heights[i]);
            while(!st.empty() && currHeight < heights[st.top()]) {
                int h = heights[st.top()]; st.pop();
                int w = st.empty() ? i : i - st.top() - 1;
                maxArea = max(maxArea, h * w);
            }
            st.push(i);
        }
        return maxArea;
    }
};
